collection.description: This collection features our conversations throughout the State of Maine held with educators, students, community members, and major Maine industry professionals. We are asking what youth will need to thrive personally, civically, and economically in the Maine of 2050. The collection is expanding daily, so check back!
collection.title: Maine ED 2050

highlights.description: Especially encouraging students to find their people through after school activities and sports.

I think the curiosity and creativity traits should be used throughout all grades and through hands-on work that the students enjoy. I learn more while having fun and being open to what is being taught.
Finding what the students like to do and want to do as a job should be more of a priority for the teachers.
Going at the students own pace as long as they can continue to learn without wasting time. Finding time management for students is important.
miscommunication kills a lot of people every year. If we as a people can talk to each other then mental health can be reduced

I feel like supporting small businesses is the best way to give back to the community. the stronger the communal shops the more tourists visit. more tourists more money spent at said small businesses stronger economy
I think for students being known and understood by the teachers is important. I think it helps the student to want to try harder when the teachers give extra support.
